      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "John Stuart Mill's harm principle provides the perfect framework; he argued that the only legitimate reason to restrict speech is to prevent direct, demonstrable harm to others, not merely to prevent offense or error. Any attempt by the state to police \"misinformation\" is a dangerous overreach because it presupposes that the government possesses the infallible knowledge to determine truth, which is inherently arrogant. Allowing the state to act as arbiter of truth immediately collapses the marketplace into a state-controlled echo chamber, destroying the very mechanism of societal progress.",
